File: platform/browser-extension/src/offscreen/index.ts, line 321-376. At the top of the async IIFE inside the ws:setUrl case (line 321), before line 322 where rawUrl is read, add a try-catch that validates rawUrl with new URL(rawUrl). Check that the protocol is 'ws:' or 'wss:'. If validation fails, log a warning and return sendResponse({ ok: true }) early. This matches the defensive pattern used by isValidWsOrigin at line 42-64 which also validates URL format. Example:

try {
  const parsed = new URL(rawUrl);
  if (parsed.protocol !== 'ws:' && parsed.protocol !== 'wss:') {
    console.warn(`[opentabs:offscreen] Rejected ws:setUrl with invalid protocol: ${parsed.protocol}`);
    sendResponse({ ok: true });
    return;
  }
} catch {
  console.warn('[opentabs:offscreen] Rejected ws:setUrl: invalid URL format');
  sendResponse({ ok: true });
  return;
}

